{SOUTH has 20 points, excellent \D stoppers and a balanced hand. 
She is two points too strong to overcall 1NT. Instead, she doubles.

NORTH has an awful hand - but since he is forced to bid he says 1\S, assuming SOUTH wants 
to hear his best suit.

SOUTH now bids 1NT, showing the balanced 19-21 point hand. NORTH passes, of course.}

