[Student "S"]
{With a 5-card \S suit and 13 points SOUTH should overcall 1\S.

NORTH has 13 points and four \Ss. If SOUTH had opened, NORTH's hand would be good enough 
to insist on game. But since SOUTH overcalled, NORTH merely invites with a jump to 3\S.

SOUTH has better than a minimum overcall so she accepts the invitation and bids 4\S.}

